[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m24[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m25[0m[39m: ***************************************************************************[0m[35m/[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m26[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m27[0m[39m:#include [0m[32m"urldata.h"[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m28[0m[39m:#include [0m[32m"curl_addrinfo.h"[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m29[0m[39m:#ifdef USE_HTTPSRR[0m                                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m2986:C[0m[39mURLMcode [0m[1;35mcurl_multi_perform[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLM *m, int *running_handles[0m[1;39m)[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2987[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2988[0m[39m:  CURLMcode returncode = CURLM_OK;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2989[0m[39m:  struct Curl_tree *t = NULL;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2990[0m[39m:  struct curltime now = [0m[1;35mCurl_now[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2991[0m[39m:  struct Curl_llist_node *e;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2992[0m[39m:  struct Curl_llist_node *n = NULL;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2993[0m[39m:  struct Curl_multi *multi = m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2994[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mSIGPIPE_VARIABLE[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpipe_st[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/multi.[0m[1;92mc:1800[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1815[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1800[0m[39m:      *protocol_done = TRUE;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1801[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1802[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* it has started, possibly even completed but that knowledge is not [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstored[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1803[0m[39m:       in this bit! *[0m[35m/[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1804[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!result[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1805[0m[39m:      conn->bits.protoconnstart = TRUE;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1806[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1807[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1808[0m[39m:  return result; [0m[35m/[0m[39m* pass back status *[0m[35m/[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1809[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1810[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1811[0m[39m:static void [0m[1;35mset_in_callback[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_multi *multi, bool value[0m[1;39m)[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1812[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1813[0m[39m:  multi->in_callback = value;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1814[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1815[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1402[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1410[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1402[0m[39m:void [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1403[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1404[0m[39m:  struct doh_probes *doh = data->req.doh;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1405[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh && data->multi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1406[0m[39m:    struct Curl_easy *probe_data;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1407[0m[39m:    curl_off_t mid;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1408[0m[39m:    size_t slot;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1409[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mfor[0m[1;39m([0m[39mslot = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; slot < DOH_SLOT_COUNT; slot++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1410[0m[39m:      mid = doh->probe[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.easy_mid;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash in Curl_doh_close arises when an internal “probe” easy handle [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mspawned by doh_run_probe[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m inherits the parent handle’s `data->req.doh` pointer. [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWhen that internal handle finishes, Curl_req_done invokes Curl_doh_close on it, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msees a non-NULL `data->req.doh` and a valid `data->multi`, then loops over the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mslots and dereferences `doh->probe[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`. However, because this internal handle [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwas never the owner of the doh_probes struct, its use of `data->req.doh` is [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvalid, and some slots may hold garbage or have been freed already—leading to a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwild‐addr read.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In short, internal probe handles must not think they “own” or should clean up [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe parent’s doh_probes struct.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Functionality[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing DoH logic, including multiple concurrent probes and parent handle[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcleanup, must remain intact.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Only internal probe handles must be prevented from running the DoH cleanup [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Proposed Patch Overview[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. In doh_run_probe [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlib/doh.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, immediately after creating the internal easy [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandle [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doh`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, clear its `req.doh` so that subsequent Curl_req_done calls on that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandle do nothing in Curl_doh_close.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Similarly, clear any other flags or fields that may trigger DoH cleanup on [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe probe handle [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. `req.waitp`, `req.new_url` if used[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Add a comment to explain why we clear `req.doh` on the probe handle to avoid [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfusion.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Detailed Steps[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Locate doh_run_probe in lib/doh.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m250[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. After the call to `[0m[1;35mCurl_open[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&doh, data->multi, data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, insert:[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* The newly created handle is a probe sub-handle. It must not[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         run Curl_doh_close on the parent's doh struct when done. *[0m[35m/[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      doh->req.doh = NULL;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. If doh_run_probe propagates the parent struct in any other fields, similarly [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreset those fields [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `doh->req.dns`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. No changes should be made to the fuzz harness or multi‐handle logic.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By nulling `doh->req.doh`, Curl_doh_close will see `doh == NULL` and exit [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediately, skipping the invalid loop.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Parent handle still has its `req.doh` intact and will perform correct cleanup [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monce its main request finishes.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This approach is minimal, targeted, and does not alter harness code, fuzz [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic, or external dependencies.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar patterns exist elsewhere in libcurl where sub-handles inherit and then[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreset parent state to isolate teardown [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., HTTP pipelining internals[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other code checks `doh->req.doh` on probe handles for operational logic; [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclearing it has no negative effect on the DoH transaction.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If future code paths rely on `data->req.doh` being non-NULL during a probe, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtests will catch regressions.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We mitigate this risk by limiting the change to immediately [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpost-initialization of the probe handle.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer run of the `curl_fuzzer_http` fuzzer triggered a segmentation [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfault in `Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1410[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when processing a single input [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimes. The crash log shows a wild read of a high address, with a call stack through[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_req_done`, `multi_done`, `curl_multi_perform`, and the fuzzer harness in [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`curl_fuzzer.cc`.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo address this, a patch was proposed in `lib/doh.c` to:  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Change the call to `Curl_open` to accept three arguments [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`&doh`, `data->multi`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Return early on error instead of `goto error`.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Invalidate the parent DOH handle by setting `doh->req.doh = NULL`.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the build failed immediately with a compiler error in [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`lib/doh.c`:  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“too many arguments to function call, expected single argument ‘curl’, have [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marguments”  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointing to the modified `[0m[1;35mCurl_open[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&doh, data->multi, data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` line.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-Wdeclaration-after-statement -Wcast-align -Wno-system-headers -Wshorten-[0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-to-[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m300[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* in debug mode, also allow http *[0m[35m/[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m301[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_PROTOCOLS, CURLPROTO_HTTP|CURLPROTO_HTTPS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m302[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m303[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_TIMEOUT_MS, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlong[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mtimeout_ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m304[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_SHARE, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLSH *[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mdata->share[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m305[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->set.err && data->set.err != stderr[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m306[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_STDERR, data->set.err[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m307[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCurl_trc_ft_is_verbose[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, &Curl_doh_trc[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m308[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_VERBOSE, 1L[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m309[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->set.no_signal[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m310[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_NOSIGNAL, 1L[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m311[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m312[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYHOST,[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m313[0m[39m:    data->set.doh_verifyhost ? 2L : 0L[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m314[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYPEER,[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m315[0m[39m:    data->set.doh_verifypeer ? 1L : 0L[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m316[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYSTATUS,[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m317[0m[39m:    data->set.doh_verifystatus ? 1L : 0L[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m318[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m319[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Inherit *some* SSL options from the user's transfer. This is a[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m320[0m[39m:     best-guess as to which options are needed for compatibility. #[0m[1;36m3661[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m321[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m322[0m[39m:     Note DoH does not inherit the user's proxy server so proxy SSL settings[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m323[0m[39m:     have no effect and are not inherited. If that changes then two new[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m324[0m[39m:     options should be added to check doh proxy insecure separately,[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m325[0m[39m:     CURLOPT_DOH_PROXY_SSL_VERIFYHOST and CURLOPT_DOH_PROXY_SSL_VERIFYPEER.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m326[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m327[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->set.ssl.falsestart[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m328[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_SSL_FALSESTART, 1L[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m329[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->set.str[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mSTRING_SSL_CAFILE[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m330[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_CAINFO,[0m                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m564[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:250[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m257[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m250[0m[39m:static CURLcode [0m[1;35mdoh_run_probe[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy *data,[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m251[0m[39m:                              struct doh_probe *p, DNStype dnstype,[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m252[0m[39m:                              const char *host,[0m                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m254[0m[39m:                              struct curl_slist *headers[0m[1;39m)[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m255[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m256[0m[39m:  struct Curl_easy *doh = NULL;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m257[0m[39m:  CURLcode result = CURLE_OK;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:378[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m392[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m378[0m[39m:  doh->set.fmultidone = doh_done;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m379[0m[39m:  doh->set.dohfor_mid = data->mid; [0m[35m/[0m[39m* for which transfer this is done *[0m[35m/[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m380[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m381[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* DoH handles must not inherit private_data. The handles may be passed to[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m382[0m[39m:     the user via callbacks and the user will be able to identify them as[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m383[0m[39m:     internal handles because private data is not set. The user can then set[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m384[0m[39m:     private_data via CURLOPT_PRIVATE if they so choose. *[0m[35m/[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m385[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mDEBUGASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!doh->set.private_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m386[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m387[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcurl_multi_add_handle[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmulti, doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m388[0m[39m:    goto error;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m389[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m390[0m[39m:  p->easy_mid = doh->mid;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m391[0m[39m:  return CURLE_OK;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m392[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The SEGV in Curl_doh_close arises because the parent `data->req.doh` struct [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremains allocated and non-NULL after the first request completes. On subsequent [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalls to `Curl_req_done`, `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` re‐enters a loop over the old [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprobes array, trying to remove sub-handles whose slots may already have been freed [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor never initialized, leading to wild memory accesses.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Core Insight from Code Snippets  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mCurl_open[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` correctly allocates a new easy handle for each DOH probe; [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mits `req.doh` pointer is initially NULL [0m[1;39m([0m[39mso sub-handles never call Curl_doh_close[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` only unlinks and closes individual DOH sub-handles but [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoes *not* free the `doh_probes` struct itself, leaving `data->req.doh` dangling.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` wraps `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, frees the header list, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand then frees and NULLs `data->req.doh`.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `Curl_req_done` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand `Curl_req_hard_reset`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m currently invoke only [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, never `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Strategy to Fix  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. In `lib/request.c`, update both request completion and hard-reset paths to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall the *full* cleanup [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich includes freeing the parent struct[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m rather than just[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe close:  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. In `[0m[1;35mCurl_req_done[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, replace:[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        #endif[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        with[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        #endif[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. In `[0m[1;35mCurl_req_hard_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, similarly replace its `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall with `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Rationale  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` calls `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, frees the probe headers and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `doh_probes` struct, and sets `data->req.doh = NULL`.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - By nullifying `data->req.doh`, subsequent calls to `Curl_req_done` will see [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mno active DOH state and skip the cleanup loop entirely, preventing wild reads.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Logic  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Probe lifecycle**: Sub-handles are still created with `[0m[1;35mCurl_open[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madded to the multi handle, and closed via `Curl_doh_close` inside [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_cleanup`.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Harness behavior**: No changes to harness, fuzzer, or test code.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Option inheritance and callback flow**: Unaffected, since only the [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparent‐handle cleanup call is changed.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Side Effects and Mitigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - There is no risk of losing DOH sub-probes prematurely: `Curl_doh_cleanup` only[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mruns after the main transfer finishes or is reset.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Double-free is avoided because `data->req.doh` becomes NULL after cleanup, and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboth `Curl_req_done` and `Curl_req_free` guard on non-NULL.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes to `doh_run_probe` or `Curl_open`, avoiding signature mismatches.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Summary  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   By calling `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` instead of `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrequest teardown paths, we ensure that the `doh_probes` struct is both closed *and*[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfreed, preventing repeated cleanup on an already freed or stale struct and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meliminating the wild-memory-read crash.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey Observations  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash remains in `Curl_doh_close` even though direct calls in `request.c` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwere switched to `Curl_doh_cleanup`.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Inside `Curl_doh_cleanup`, the first action is still to call `Curl_doh_close`, so[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe underlying faulty behavior in `Curl_doh_close` is still triggered.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack always includes the fuzzer harness invoking `curl_multi_perform` → [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`multi_done` → `Curl_req_done` → DNS-over-HTTPS cleanup.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **lib/doh.c**  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The implementation of `Curl_doh_close` around line [0m[1;36m1410[0m[39m: what pointer or data [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructure is being dereferenced?  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The relationship between `Curl_doh_cleanup` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline ~[0m[1;36m1435[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close`—what state checks happen before calling `Curl_doh_close`?  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Request Lifecycle in lib/request.c**  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How and when the DOH context is initialized, stored in `data`, and [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubsequently cleaned up.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether `data` or members of its `req` substructure [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., a DOH handle[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m can [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe null, uninitialized, or already freed at the time cleanup is called.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Multi-handle Path [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlib/multi.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How `multi_done` and `multi_runsingle` orchestrate individual request cleanup;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mverify they do not invoke cleanup twice or in an invalid order.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Fuzzer Harness Code**  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Although not the root cause, review `fuzz_handle_transfer` to see if it [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmanipulates or resets `data` in a way that leaves DOH pointers in an invalid state.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA holistic view requires tracing the full DOH handle life cycle from creation [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrough all code paths to its final closure. This should reveal why [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close` is accessing invalid memory and how cleanup should be reordered or[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguarded.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m93[0m[39m:  const char *hostp = host;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m95[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* The expected output length is [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes more than the length of[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m96[0m[39m:   * the QNAME-encoding of the hostname.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m97[0m[39m:   *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m98[0m[39m:   * A valid DNS name may not contain a zero-length label, except at[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m99[0m[39m:   * the end. For this reason, a name beginning with a dot, or[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100[0m[39m:   * containing a sequence of two or more consecutive dots, is invalid[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m101[0m[39m:   * and cannot be encoded as a QNAME.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m102[0m[39m:   *[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m103[0m[39m:   * If the hostname ends with a trailing dot, the corresponding[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m104[0m[39m:   * QNAME-encoding is one byte longer than the hostname. If [0m[1;39m([0m[39mas is[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m105[0m[39m:   * also valid[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m the hostname is shortened by the omission of the[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m106[0m[39m:   * trailing dot, then its QNAME-encoding will be two bytes longer[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m107[0m[39m:   * than the hostname.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m108[0m[39m:   *[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m109[0m[39m:   * Each [0m[1;39m[[0m[39m label, dot [0m[1;39m][0m[39m pair is encoded as [0m[1;39m[[0m[39m length, label [0m[1;39m][0m[39m,[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m110[0m[39m:   * preserving overall length. A final [0m[1;39m[[0m[39m label [0m[1;39m][0m[39m without a dot is[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m111[0m[39m:   * also encoded as [0m[1;39m[[0m[39m length, label [0m[1;39m][0m[39m, increasing overall length[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m112[0m[39m:   * by one. The encoding is completed by appending a zero byte,[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m113[0m[39m:   * representing the zero-length root label, again increasing[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m114[0m[39m:   * the overall length by one.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m115[0m[39m:   *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m116[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m117[0m[39m:  size_t expected_len;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m118[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mDEBUGASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mhostlen[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m119[0m[39m:  expected_len = [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m + hostlen + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m120[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mhost[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mhostlen-[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m!=[0m[32m'.'[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m122[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m123[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mexpected_len > [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m256[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m16[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[39m* RFCs [0m[1;36m1034[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m1035[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m98[0m[39m:   * A valid DNS name may not contain a zero-length label, except at[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m99[0m[39m:   * the end. For this reason, a name beginning with a dot, or[0m                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m107[0m[39m:   * than the hostname.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m108[0m[39m:   *[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m109[0m[39m:   * Each [0m[1;39m[[0m[39m label, dot [0m[1;39m][0m[39m pair is encoded as [0m[1;39m[[0m[39m length, label [0m[1;39m][0m[39m,[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m110[0m[39m:   * preserving overall length. A final [0m[1;39m[[0m[39m label [0m[1;39m][0m[39m without a dot is[0m              [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m272[0m[39m:    goto error;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m273[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m274[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* [0m[1;35mCurl_open[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is the internal version of [0m[1;35mcurl_easy_init[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m275[0m[39m:  result = [0m[1;35mCurl_open[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m276[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mresult[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m277[0m[39m:    goto error;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m278[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m279[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* pass in the struct pointer via a local variable to please coverity and[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m280[0m[39m:     the gcc typecheck helpers *[0m[35m/[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m281[0m[39m:  doh->state.internal = TRUE;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m282[0m[39m:#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_VERBOSE_STRINGS[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m283[0m[39m:  doh->state.feat = &Curl_doh_trc;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m284[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m285[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_URL, url[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m286[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_DEFAULT_PROTOCOL, [0m[32m"https"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m287[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_WRITEFUNCTION, doh_write_cb[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m288[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_WRITEDATA, &p->resp_body[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m289[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_[0m[1;33mPOST[0m[39mFIELDS, p->req_body[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m290[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_[0m[1;33mPOST[0m[39mFIELDSIZE, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlong[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mp->req_body_len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m291[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_HTTP[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER, headers[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m292[0m[39m:#ifdef USE_HTTP2[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m293[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_HTTP_VERSION, CURL_HTTP_VERSION_2TLS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m294[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_PIPEWAIT, 1L[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m295[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m296[0m[39m:#ifndef DEBUGBUILD[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m297[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* enforce HTTPS if not debug *[0m[35m/[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m298[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_PROTOCOLS, CURLPROTO_HTTPS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m299[0m[39m:#else[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m300[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* in debug mode, also allow http *[0m[35m/[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m301[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_PROTOCOLS, CURLPROTO_HTTP|CURLPROTO_HTTPS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m302[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m303[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_TIMEOUT_MS, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlong[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mtimeout_ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m304[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_SHARE, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLSH *[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mdata->share[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m305[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->set.err && data->set.err != stderr[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m306[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_STDERR, data->set.err[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m307[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCurl_trc_ft_is_verbose[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, &Curl_doh_trc[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m308[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_VERBOSE, 1L[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m309[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->set.no_signal[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m310[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_NOSIGNAL, 1L[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m311[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m312[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYHOST,[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m313[0m[39m:    data->set.doh_verifyhost ? 2L : 0L[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m314[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYPEER,[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m315[0m[39m:    data->set.doh_verifypeer ? 1L : 0L[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m316[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYSTATUS,[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m317[0m[39m:    data->set.doh_verifystatus ? 1L : 0L[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m318[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m319[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Inherit *some* SSL options from the user's transfer. This is a[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m320[0m[39m:     best-guess as to which options are needed for compatibility. #[0m[1;36m3661[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m321[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m322[0m[39m:     Note DoH does not inherit the user's proxy server so proxy SSL settings[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m323[0m[39m:     have no effect and are not inherited. If that changes then two new[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m324[0m[39m:     options should be added to check doh proxy insecure separately,[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m325[0m[39m:     CURLOPT_DOH_PROXY_SSL_VERIFYHOST and CURLOPT_DOH_PROXY_SSL_VERIFYPEER.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m326[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m327[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->set.ssl.falsestart[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m328[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_SSL_FALSESTART, 1L[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m329[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->set.str[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mSTRING_SSL_CAFILE[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m330[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_CAINFO,[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m331[0m[39m:                       data->set.str[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mSTRING_SSL_CAFILE[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m332[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m333[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->set.blobs[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mBLOB_CAINFO[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m334[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_CAINFO_BLOB,[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m335[0m[39m:                       data->set.blobs[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mBLOB_CAINFO[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m336[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m337[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->set.str[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mSTRING_SSL_CAPATH[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m338[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_CAPATH,[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m339[0m[39m:                       data->set.str[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mSTRING_SSL_CAPATH[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m340[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m341[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->set.str[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mSTRING_SSL_CRLFILE[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m342[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_CRLFILE,[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m343[0m[39m:                       data->set.str[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mSTRING_SSL_CRLFILE[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m344[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m345[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->set.ssl.certinfo[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m346[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_CERTINFO, 1L[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m347[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->set.ssl.fsslctx[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m348[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_SSL_CTX_FUNCTION, data->set.ssl.fsslctx[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m349[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->set.ssl.fsslctxp[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m350[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mERROR_CHECK_SETOPT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLOPT_SSL_CTX_DATA, data->set.ssl.fsslctxp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
